ðŸ’¡ **Q.3** Differentiate between HTML Tags and Elements?

HTML tags:
1.HTML tags are the building blocks of an HTML document and are used to define the structure and layout of web content.
2.Tags are represented by angle brackets (<>) and are placed before and after the content they are defining.
3.HTML tags are the individual markers that define the beginning and end of an element
4.tags are the specific markers that define the boundaries and behavior of those elements.

HTML Element:
1.HTML elements are composed of HTML tags
2.An HTML element is everything from the start tag (<tag>) to the end tag (</tag>), including the content in between.
3.HTML elements consist of the tags, the content they enclose, and any associated attributes. 
4.complete units of structure and content in an HTML document

