ðŸ’¡ **Q.8** What is the difference between <figure> tag and <img> tag?

img:
1.The <img> tag is a self-closing tag used to embed images into an HTML document.
2.It does not have a closing tag and is written in the following format: <img src="image.jpg" alt="Description of the image">.

<figure>:
1.The <figure> tag is a block-level element used to encapsulate media content, such as images, illustrations, diagrams, audio, video, etc along with their optional captions.
2.<figure>
  <img src="example.jpg" alt="A beautiful sunset">
  <figcaption>A beautiful sunset at the beach.</figcaption>
</figure>


